RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Claiming Price $12,500 Indiana bred maidens and I ndiana claiming races for $15,000 or less not considered in eligibility.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKET DOCKET vied for the lead from between rivals through the turn, lost some ground into the lane, stayed on well to inched up late and prevail. NEOKING saved ground through the turn and into the when never far back, shifted off the inside approaching the sixteenth pole, moved to the four path late and was up for the place spot while gaining to the wire. ETERNAL BLISS vied for the lead along the inside of two others through the turn, had his largest lead with an eighth to go then could not hold and lost the place spot at the wire. SMART DRESSER pressed the pace three wide and in the four path through the turn, came into the lane from the five path and weakened. BOOGIE BODE chased the three rival duel through the turn while in the four path, came into the lane from the five path and lacked the needed response. AZTECA STAR was close early into the turn then steadily gave ground. GOT THE BOB stumbled at the start, raced in the back and was never in it.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 43000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 7 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPOTONJUSTICE dueled outside of a rival, bid near the three-eighths pole to go clear, then came out under left-handed encouragement near the sixteenth pole to bump PICKLE FEET hard and cause that one to take one, then lasted under steady urging. PICKLE FEET stalked the pace in the three path, bid at the eighth pole, was bumped and taken up near the sixteenth pole when SPOTONJUSTICE came out and closed late. CABOOSE raced in the five path and had no late bid. GOOD FOREVER saved ground to no avail. ONE WAY RAY dueled inside, then faded on the turn. HIGHCOTTON JUSTICE stalked the pace in the three path before giving way at the quarter pole. SPOTONJUSTICE WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED SECOND FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY AND AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF PICKLEFEET AGAINST SPOTONJUSTICE CONCERNING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 36 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONLY EMOTIONS set the pace into the first turn, continued on a clear lead while near the inside, widened through the turn and into the lane, was asked for more after straightening in the lane and drew off. JANEY CREED was unhurried while off the inside, angled into the five path through the turn when gaining momentum, continued with a good run into the lane while in the six path and stayed on well to be up for the place spot while not a threat to the winner. LILMORECRAKEN settled off the pace while near the inside, bid into the turn to be a threat, continued near the inside into the lane when moving closest to the winner then lost the place late. MS QUALITY CONTROL raced in the two path into the far turn when gaining momentum, checked when in tight near the inside, swung into the lane from the five or six path when gaining energy, shifted into the two path through the drive and was gaining. VINO ROSATO trailed early while off the inside, bid from the six path through late turn, came into the lane from the seven path and finished evenly. TAAMUQ raced between while in the two path through the far turn and tired after straightening in the lane. PERFECT MANHATTAN was close up early to chase the winner into the backstretch, steadily retreated along the inside to trail the field through the far turn, swung into the lane from the five path and passed tired ones. SELES never a factor while along the inside. HOUSEFLY (IRE) chased the pace from the four path into the far turn then was empty turning into the lane. DON'T TOUCH chased the pace from the two path into the far turn then was suddenly done in late turn. SENSIBLE CHOICE raced five wide through the first turn, continued in the five path down the backstretch and into the far turn and had nothing for the drive. HAZIEL chased the winner from the three path into the lane then retreated.

(Rail at 36feet).

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GET BACK GOLDIE saved ground throughout, cut the corner into the lane when leaders drifted off rail, quickly cleared on the lead and was under a drive to hold. ARTURO TOSCANINI (IRE) raced near the rail when near the back, moved up through the turn, followed the winner into the lane while cutting the corner, could not gain on the top one while winning the duel for the place spot. HEMP HEAVEN was near the rail throughout, came into the lane from the three path, dueled for the place spot and just missed while slowly gaining on the top one. FOUNDER trailed for half when in the two path, was still well back into the lane, gained momentum from the five path, split rivals near the sixteenth pole and finished willingly. CIRCLE BACK JACK chased the pace from the three path into the turn, continued as a serious threat into the lane then weakened late. MUTAKATIF (IRE) raced in the three or four path through the turn when in mid-pack, came into the lane from the six path, was seven wide in deep stretch and never was a serious threat. ELUSIVE TARGET raced in the three path through the far turn when near the back, came into the lane from the five path and never was a serious menace. AUTHORITARIAN vied for the lead through the turn and into the lane, came off the inside into the lane, chased the winner while straightening then faded. NIP N TUCK vied for the lead two wide through the turn, was floated into the four path into the lane then gave way. RICH KINGDOM chased the pace from the four path down the backstretch and was done entering the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SANTIVA DIVA pressed the early pace outside of the leader, shifted to the rail on the turn, dueled inside of that one, was clear late and lasted under steady handling. KAYS HEAVENLY STAR raced inside, bid in early stretch and brushed with a rival, then rallied late and missed. JANE'S A DIVA bore in at the start, led in the two path, dueled through the stretch and was no match. ECHO DREAMER raced in the four path, bid in early stretch, bumped a foe and gained fourth. MALI BALI raced in the five path and had a mild late bid. GOLDEN HEIST was off awkwardly, saved ground and had a mild late bid. EMERSON'S DREAM was bumped at the start, was unrushed, bid at the quarter pole, the was bumped and checked at the eighth pole. MUST BE A MIRACLE passed tired foes. COMP saved ground to no avail. YOU'RE SO AWESOME stalked the pace in the three path and was steadied at the three-sixteenths pole. GRANNY REWARD was not a factor. ECHO DREAMER WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED NINTH AFTER EMERSON'S DREAM LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST ECHO DREAMER AND KAYS HEAVENLY STAR FOR INTERFERENCE IN EARLY STRETCH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VICTOR'S DEAL chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, bid in late turn, moved to challenge the leader into the lane, dueled with that one through the final eighth and edged up late. C F V TEXAS RED vied for the lead while two wide, cleared down the backstretch and into the turn, was joined by the winner into the lane, dueled through the lane while along the rail and could not keep up late while clearly second best. MONUMENTALJUSTICE saved ground early while unhurried, moved off the inside in mid-turn, continued into the three path for the drive and moved up to be best of the rest. DEVILS GOTTA GO saved ground into the far turn, was asked for more in late turn then lacked a closing response. PAYNTER'S CANVAS vied for the lead early while along the inside, chased the pacesetter into the turn and faded through the lane. FOXY BOXY raced in the two path through the turn and was empty through the lane. FOREVER FRIENDS trailed through the far turn then passed a couple tired ones. LOONY raced in the two path through the turn and was empty into the lane. CUPID'S RUNAWAY was in the three or four path into the far turn and was done soon after.
